<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Durham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Fort au
                                    Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-01-18"><hi rend="italic">January 18, 1893</hi></date>.
                            (Received January 18.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Durham, replying to Mr. Foster’s telegram, explains that a resort to
                        force will not be necessary, but insists on the necessity of having the
                        presence and cooperation of the <hi rend="italic">Atlanta.</hi></p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>